    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="On 03 August 2020, IOM’s DTM program carried out an assessment to ascertain the level of damage sustained in camps and camp-like settings due to heavy windstorm and rainfall on the 2nd of August 2020. Overall, 9 camps were affected in Bama, Jere, Maiduguri and Konduga LGAs. The worst-hit of the camps assessed was the Faria Gidan Block camp in Jere LGA where a heavy rainfall left 115 makeshift shelters damaged and an estimated 345 individuals without shelter due to flooding. Other affected camps are: GSSS Camp Bama in Bama LGA, Borgoza Camp in Maiduguri Metropolitan Council, Federal Training Center Camp (Dalori I) Camp, 400 Housing Estate (Gubio Camp) in Konduga LGA and Madinatu Camp, Al-Yakub Camp, El-miskin Center, Fulatari Camp in Jere LGA."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1547 1560 1573 1586 1599 1612 1625 1638 1651 1664 1677 1690 1703 1716 1729 1742 1755 1768 1781 1794 1807 1820 1833 1846 1859 1872 1885 1898 1911 1924 1929 1934 1953 1958 2011 1963 1968 1973 1978 2023 2028 1946 1939 2004 2016 1983 1990 1997 2033 2047 2040 2043 2050 2054 2067"/>
